ry effort by the us food service industry to reduce salt in processed foods could prevent strokes and heart attacks in nearly a million americans and saving $32.1 billion in medical costs population strategies to decrease sodium intake and the burden of cardiovascular disease a cost effectiveness analysis search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest crystal smith spangler va fellow with an expertise in sodium and organics june 23 2010 news in new england journal commentary shp director alan garber explores the role of fda in regulating devices march 24 2010 announcement proposed industry effort to reduce salt in food could save lives money shp va study shows march 2 2010 press release garber's iom committee releases report recommending 100 initial priorities for research to determine which health care approaches work best june 30 2009 press release news article on bush healthcare priorities cites mcclellan kessler study on malpractice caps november 19 2004 in the news webmd cites low carb diet study in 2003 top food trends in the news webmd on december 16 2003 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
